All: Not to be confused with shape, a diamond’s cut rating tells you how well its proportions interact with light. By evaluating the angles and proportions of the diamond, the cut grade is designed to tell you how sparkly and brilliant your stone is. Cut grading is usually not available for fancy shapes (any shape that is not round), because the mathematical formula that determines light return becomes less reliable when different length to width ratios are factored in.
全部: 為作不要與形狀混淆，鑽石的切工等級解釋光線的相互作用程度。 通過評估鑽石的角度和比例，切工等級解釋鑽石有多閃亮。 切工分級通常不適用於花形或任何非圓形的形，因為當考慮到不同的長寬，確定光返變得不那麼可靠。

All: The color scale measures the degree of colorlessness in a diamond. D is the highest and most colorless grade, but also the most expensive. To get the most value for your budget, look for an eye colorless stone. For most diamonds, this is in the F-H range.
全部: 衡量鑽石色標測量無色程度。 D是最高、最無色的等級，但也是最貴的, 尋找無色眼睛的寶石。最化算是大多數鑽石是在 F-H 範圍內。

All: A diamond’s clarity refers to the tiny traces of natural elements that are trapped inside the stone. 99% of diamonds contain inclusions or flaws. You do not need a flawless diamond - they are very rare and expensive - but you want to look for one that is perfect to the naked eye. Depending on the shape of the diamond, the sweet spot for clarity is usually between VVS2 to SI1.
全部: 鑽石的淨度是指被困在石頭內自然元素微小痕跡。 99% 的鑽石含有內含物或瑕疵。 您不需要完美無瑕的鑽石因為它們非常稀有且昂貴。 但您想要尋找一顆肉眼可見的完美鑽石。 根據鑽石的形狀，淨度的最佳點通常在 VVS2 到 SI1 之間。

All: Depth percentage is the height of the diamond measured from the culet to the table, divided by the width of the diamond. The lower the depth %, the larger the diamond will appear (given the same weight), but if this number is too low then the brilliance of the diamond will be sacrificed. The depth percentage is one of the elements that determines the Cut grading.
全部: 深度百分比是鑽石從底尖到桌面的高度除以鑽石的寬度。 深度百分比越低，鑽石就會顯得越大（在重量相同的情況下），但如果這個數字太低，那麼鑽石的亮度就會受到影響。 深度百分比是決定切工分級的元素之一。

All: Table percentage is the width of a diamond’s largest facet (the table) divided by its overall width. It tells you how big the “face” of a diamond is.
全部: 檯面百分比是鑽石最大刻面（檯面）的寬度除以總寬度。 它告訴您鑽石的“面”有多大。

All: Polish describes how smooth the surface of a diamond is. Aim for an Excellent or Very Good polish rating.
全部: 拋光描述鑽石表面光滑程度。 取獲得優秀或非常好的拋光評級。

All: Symmetry describes how symmetrical the diamond is cut all the way around, which is a contributing factor to a diamond’s sparkle and brilliance. Aim for an Excellent or Very Good symmetry rating for round brilliant shapes, and Excellent to Good for fancy shapes.
全部: 對稱描述了鑽石在整個切割過程中的對稱性，這是影響鑽石閃耀度和亮度的一個因素。 圓形明亮式形狀的對稱性評級為優秀或非常好，花式形狀的對稱性評級為優秀至良好。

All: Carat is a unit of measurement to determine a diamond’s weight. Typically, a higher carat weight means a larger looking diamond, but that is not always the case. Look for the mm measurements of the diamond to determine its visible size.
全部: 卡是確定鑽石重量的計量單位。 一般來說更高卡代表更大的鑽石，但情況並非每次一樣。查看鑽石的毫米尺寸以確定其可見尺寸。

All: Fluorescence tells you how a diamond responds to ultraviolet light - does it glow under a black light? Diamonds with no fluorescence are generally priced higher on the market, but it is rare for fluorescence to have any visual impact on the diamond; some fluorescence can even enhance the look of the stone.Our site recommends searching for diamonds with none to medium fluorescence, and keeping open the option of strong fluorescence for additional value.
全部: 螢光告訴您鑽石對紫外線的反應 - 它在黑光下會發光嗎？ 沒有螢光的鑽石在市場上一般價格較高，但螢光對鑽石產生任何視覺影響的情況很少見； 一些螢光甚至可以增強鑽石的外觀。我們的網站建議搜索沒有到中等螢光的鑽石，並保持打開強螢光選項以獲得附加價值。

All: Depth percentage is the height of the diamond measured from the culet to the table, divided by the width of the diamond. The lower the depth %, the larger the diamond will appear (given the same weight), but if this number is too low then the brilliance of the diamond will be sacrificed. The depth percentage is one of the elements that determines the Cut grading.
全部: 深度百分比是鑽石從底尖到桌面的高度除以鑽石的寬度。 深度百分比越低，鑽石就會顯得越大（在重量相同的情況下），但如果這個數字太低，那麼鑽石的亮度就會受到影響。 深度百分比是決定切工分級的元素之一。

All: Formed over billions of years, natural diamonds are mined from the earth. Diamonds are the hardest mineral on earth, which makes them an ideal material for daily wear over a lifetime. Our natural diamonds are conflict-free and GIA certified.
全部: 天然鑽石形成於數十億年，是從地球中開采出來的。 鑽石是地球上最堅硬的礦物，這使它們成為終生日常佩戴的理想材料。 我們的天然鑽石無衝突並獲得 GIA 認證。

All: Also known as fancy color diamonds, these are diamonds with colors that extend beyond GIA’s D-Z color grading scale. They fall all over the color spectrum, with a range of intensities and saturation. The most popular colors are pink and yellow.
全部: 稱為彩色鑽石，這些鑽石的顏色超出 GIA 的 D-Z 顏色分級標準。 它們遍布整個色譜，具有一系列強度和飽和度。 最受歡迎的顏色是粉紅色和黃色。

All: Lab-grown diamonds are created in a lab by replicating the high heat and high pressure environment that causes a natural diamond to form. They are compositionally identical to natural mined diamonds (hardness, density, light refraction, etc), and the two look exactly the same. A lab-grown diamond is an attractive alternative for those seeking a product with less environmental footprint.
全部: 實驗室培育鑽石是在實驗室中通過複製致天然鑽石形成的高溫和高壓環境來製造的。 它們在成分上與天然開采的鑽石相同（硬度、密度、光折射等），並且兩者看起來完全相同。 對於那些尋求環保產品的人來說，實驗室培育的鑽石是一種有吸引力代品。
